narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: A much better understanding of the history of thinking behind development.
My knowledge about the history of the discourse on development grew.
I developed a very good summary understanding of major theories and scholars in the field of international politics and development theory. This was a very good and foundational course to take.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: It was useful that the instructor provided brief framing introduction to each session. The course also allowed for open exploration.
Weakness was that readings were sometimes disconnected

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Maybe. I'm not that into philosophy but it is good as a theoretical backgrounder. I don't know if I would recommend it to someone in their second year unless they were really into this stuff.
Yes, it is a great way to discuss and think about the philosophical underpinnings of topics you spend a lot of time with, but don't question.
